President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key positions in his administration. 

1. Gordon D. Sondland: Trump intends to nominate Sondland as the Representative of the United States of America to the European Union, with the rank and status of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary. Sondland is the Founder, Chairman, and CEO of Aspen Lodging Group, LLC, and has a background in investment funds and advisory boards. He has also served as the Senior Republican advisor to the Democratic Governor of Oregon.

2. Tibor Peter Nagy Jr.: Nagy is being nominated as an Assistant Secretary of State for African Affairs. He is a retired career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has served as a U.S. Ambassador to Ethiopia and Guinea. Nagy has extensive experience in Africa and currently teaches about the continent at Texas Tech University.

3. Robert Charles O’Brien: O’Brien is being appointed as the Special Presidential Envoy for Hostage Affairs. He is an attorney, diplomat, and author, and has expertise in national security and foreign policy matters. O’Brien has served as an arbitrator in international proceedings and has been named one of the top lawyers in California.

These nominations and appointments are subject to confirmation by the relevant authorities.